items.title: Brickipedia
items.headline: Brickipedia, the LEGO wiki
items.desc: Brickipedia is a popular, well-known website, consisting of over 32k pages and counting, with users who strive to show off their knowledge for LEGO. Brickipedia, located at lego.wikia.com, is Wikia's largest LEGO Wiki, which was founded on March 4, 2005. Brickipedia's goal is to provide a free online Encyclopedia on everything LEGO. Twelve years after it was established, Brickipedia has reached a size of over 30,000 articles, and has a few hundred active users right now. Join the community and share your love of LEGO today.

items.name: Brikifilms
items.title: Brikifilms
items.headline: Welcome to Brikifilms!
items.desc:
This wiki is dedicated to the art of Brickfilming, which is (primarily) stop-motion animation created using LEGO pieces or other similar building construction toys such as Megablocks.

Stop by and find out about the history of Brickfilming, how to make a Brickfilm or to learn about Brickfilms spanning more than an hour! 

We hope you learn something new!

items.desc: Lego Bricks Wiki is a starter wiki for learning and exploring all things lego.
